    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="689"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/576</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shea</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-12T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 13, 7.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>After first official reception of diplomatic corps by Foreign Minister this
                    afternoon, had conference with him complying with Department’s instruction June
                        [<hi rend="italic">September</hi>] 9, 6 p.m. He said that Government was
                    seriously considering the acquisition of the German vessels not damaged without
                    delay and would then take up the question of utilizing the others, that they
                    were anxious to cooperate with United States in maintaining commerce. Would
                    inform me at once when plan had been worked out. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
